The paper deals with the problem of defining the significance of an itemset, which is a common topic in data mining and machine learning. The use of Maximum Entropy and Kullback-Leibler divergence suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The focus on itemsets and their frequencies suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Data Mining (cs.DM). The use of statistical tests and models suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
